{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 18:26:40.566199", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission successful.\n\nSummary of submitted solution:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- localized faulty devices: server_access_router, server_network_10.200.0.0/24\n- root cause selected: p4_table_entry_missing\n\nNotes:\n- The diagnostic concluded that the backend web servers are directly reachable from user hosts due to a policy/configuration gap — effectively missing enforcement rules. I mapped that to the available root-cause type p4_table_entry_missing (missing data-plane/forwarding rules that would enforce isolation), and localized the fault to the server_access_router and the server subnet (10.200.0.0/24). If you want, I can now proceed to gather ACLs/firewall rules, inspect load balancer and backend host firewall config, or run traceroutes to produce a remediation plan.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2223, "output_tokens": 169, "total_tokens": 2392, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
